# Future Licensing Decision

## Purpose

The Elastic Governance Layer (EGL) repository is being released initially as a public specification repository.

The final licensing model for documentation, technical specifications, reference implementations, and source code will be determined at a later stage as the project matures.

This phased approach allows the framework to establish a stable conceptual and technical foundation before adopting long-term licensing arrangements.

---

## Current Position

At the current stage:

- the repository serves primarily as an academic and governance specification project;
- the White Paper and specification documents establish the normative architecture of EGL;
- future software components, schemas, and reference implementations remain under development.

Accordingly, the documentation and future technical components may ultimately adopt different licensing strategies where appropriate.

---

## Future Considerations

Future licensing decisions may distinguish among:

- documentation and white papers;
- technical specifications;
- machine-readable schemas;
- reference implementations;
- software components;
- commercial implementation guidance.

The selected licensing model should support:

- academic citation;
- responsible research use;
- institutional adoption;
- long-term governance of the framework;
- protection of the integrity of the official EGL specification.

---

## Repository Policy

The final licensing structure will be documented through the repository's official `LICENSE` file and associated documentation once the project reaches a more mature stage of development.

Until then, all materials remain subject to the copyright notice and repository governance policies.
